Package neureka.backend.api.algorithms.fun

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    ADAgentSupplier
    Implementations of this functional interface ought to return a new instance of the ADAgent class responsible for performing automatic differentiation both for forward and backward mode differentiation.
    BackwardADPredicate
    A BackwardADPredicate lambda checks if backward mode auto differentiation (also known as back-propagation) can be performed for a given ExecutionCall.
    ExecutionDispatcher
    The ExecutionDispatcher lambda is the most important procedure within an Algorithm, which is responsible for electing an ImplementationFor the chosen Device in a given ExecutionCall passed to the ExecutionDispatcher.
    ExecutionPreparation
    An Algorithm will typically produce a result when executing an ExecutionCall.
    ForwardADPredicate
    A ForwardADPredicate lambda checks if forward mode auto differentiation can be performed for a given ExecutionCall.
    SuitabilityPredicate
    The SuitabilityPredicate checks if a given instance of an ExecutionCall is suitable to be executed in ImplementationFor residing in this Algorithm as components.
